revisions.description: Additions to allow for VPP containers. Add extremeVMDetailTable Add extremeVMPortConfigTable deprecate extremeVMVPP2PolicyTable deprecate extremeVMMappingIngressVPPName deprecate extremeVMMappingEgressVPPName deprecate extremeVMDetectedIngrssVPPName deprecate extremeVMDetectedEgressVPPName Add varbinds to extremeVMDetectResult notification extremeVMDetectedOperStatus extremeVMDetectedIngErrPolicies extremeVMDetectedEgrErrPolicies, extremeVMDetectedVPPResult, extremeVMDetectedVPPName Add varbind to extremeVMMapped extremeVMMappingVPPName Add varbind to extremeVMUnMapped extremeVMMappingVPPName removed DEFVAL from extremeVMFTPPathName Added new enumeration for extremeVMMappingStatus

extremeVM.description: Extreme Network Virtual Machine Management MIB

VMVPPSynchType.name: VMVPPSynchType
VMVPPSynchType.description: The type of policy synchronization. global -- all network policies are synchronized specific -- a single network policy is synchronized

CounterDirection.name: CounterDirection
CounterDirection.description: This direction in which the dynamic ACL counter neesd to be installed. ingress-only - counter for only ingress direction egress-only - counter for only egress direction both - counter for both ingress/egress direction none - counter not needed for either direction.

extremeVMFTPServerTable.name: extremeVMFTPServerTable
extremeVMFTPServerTable.description: The FTP servers defined for this switch

extremeVMFTPServerEntry.name: extremeVMFTPServerEntry
extremeVMFTPServerEntry.description: The FTP server entry for this switch

extremeVMFTPServerType.name: extremeVMFTPServerType
extremeVMFTPServerType.description: The type of the FTP server. The backup server is contacted if the primary fails to respond.

extremeVMFTPAddrType.name: extremeVMFTPAddrType
extremeVMFTPAddrType.description: The IP type of IP address.

extremeVMFTPServer.name: extremeVMFTPServer
extremeVMFTPServer.description: The IP Address of the FTP server used for transferring various management files.

extremeVMFTPSynchInterval.name: extremeVMFTPSynchInterval
extremeVMFTPSynchInterval.description: The time in minutes between automatic synchronization attempts. A value of 0 indicates that automatic synchronizations are not performed. Note that each switch will not perform a synchronization at exactly the time configured, but will vary the synchronization interval between 3/4 and 5/4 of the configured interval. This will avoid the situation where all switches in a network attempt a synchronizationat exactly the same moment. Other than value of 0 value of 40-3600 can be configured as interval. Automatic synchronization is disabled by default, and requests to enable them are rejected until the FTP server information (IP or IPv6 Address, Username, and Password) is configured.

extremeVMFTPRowStatus.name: extremeVMFTPRowStatus
extremeVMFTPRowStatus.description: There can only be two entries in this table, on each for primary and secondary FTP servers

extremeVMFTPPathName.name: extremeVMFTPPathName
extremeVMFTPPathName.description: The FTP server directory name for the policies to be synchronized. A value of '/pub' will be used by default for anonymous users and value of '/' will be used for other users

extremeVMFTPUsername.name: extremeVMFTPUsername
extremeVMFTPUsername.description: A valid username on the FTP server.

extremeVMFTPPassword.name: extremeVMFTPPassword
extremeVMFTPPassword.description: The Password associated with the FTP user. This object will return a zero length string when queried

extremeVMFTPPolicyDir.name: extremeVMFTPPolicyDir
extremeVMFTPPolicyDir.description: The server directory name for the policies to be synchronized. A value of '/' will be used by default

extremeVMLastSynch.name: extremeVMLastSynch
extremeVMLastSynch.description: The timestamp of the most recent synchronization attempt

extremeVMLastSynchStatus.name: extremeVMLastSynchStatus
extremeVMLastSynchStatus.description: The result of the most recent synchronization attempt. success(1) - indicates that the synchronization completed successfully accessDenied(2) - The username and password were not accepted by the server serverTimeout(3) - Could not establish a file transfer session with the configured server serverNotConfigured(4) - The server configuration is not complete

extremeVMSynchAdminState.name: extremeVMSynchAdminState
extremeVMSynchAdminState.description: Triggers a synchronization cycle on demand. A synchronization will automatically download new or updated policies as well as delete policies to match those on the server. idle(1) is returned whenever this object is read. synchronizeNow(2) triggers an immediate synchronization, and will be reflected in extremeVMSynchOperState. Attempts to set this variable to synchronizeNow(2) will be rejected if a synchronization is currently in progress.

extremeVMSynchOperState.name: extremeVMSynchOperState
extremeVMSynchOperState.description: Indicates if a synchronization is in progress, either on-demand or automatic

extremeVMTrackingEnabled.name: extremeVMTrackingEnabled
extremeVMTrackingEnabled.description: The VM tracking feature is disabled by default, and can be enabled using this object.

extremeVMPortConfigTable.name: extremeVMPortConfigTable
extremeVMPortConfigTable.description: Configures the VM features on each port.

extremeVMPortConfigEntry.name: extremeVMPortConfigEntry
extremeVMPortConfigEntry.description: An entry in the table for VM features on each port.

extremeVMPortConfigIfIndex.name: extremeVMPortConfigIfIndex
extremeVMPortConfigIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex of a physical port capable of supporting the VM Tracking features

extremeVMPortConfigVMTrackingEnabled.name: extremeVMPortConfigVMTrackingEnabled
extremeVMPortConfigVMTrackingEnabled.description: Enables the VM Tracking feature on a port. The VM Tracking feature is disabled by default

extremeVMPortConfigVMTrackingDynVlanEnab.name: extremeVMPortConfigVMTrackingDynVlanEnabled
extremeVMPortConfigVMTrackingDynVlanEnab.description: Enables the VM Tracking Dynamic VLAN feature on a port. This feature is disabled by default. VM Tracking feature must be enabled before enabling this feature.

extremeVMVPPTable.name: extremeVMVPPTable
extremeVMVPPTable.description: This table contains Port Policies contained within this switch. Port Policies come in two variants: network and local. Network policies are downloaded from the FTP server; local policies reside only within a single switch.

extremeVMVPPEntry.name: extremeVMVPPEntry
extremeVMVPPEntry.description: An entry in the table of VM policy information of this device. This table is populated with two sets of policies, those downloaded from the policy server and those defined locally on this switch.

extremeVMVPPType.name: extremeVMVPPType
extremeVMVPPType.description: The type of the port profile. Network port profiles are obtained from a central policy store. Local policies are specific to this particular switch.

extremeVMVPPName.name: extremeVMVPPName
extremeVMVPPName.description: The name of the Port VPP. VPP names must be alpha-numeric and must start with an alpha character.

extremeVMVPPControl.name: extremeVMVPPControl
extremeVMVPPControl.description: Performs the requested operation on this policy. synchronizeNow(1) will download a copy of the policy from the FTP server. (Network policies only) This object will return noOperation(2) if read.

extremeVMVPPRowStatus.name: extremeVMVPPRowStatus
extremeVMVPPRowStatus.description: Only local VPPs can be created or deleted.

extremeVMVPPCounter.name: extremeVMVPPCounter
extremeVMVPPCounter.description: This object specifies whether the VM gets attached to this VPP needs to install dynamic counters to count packets source MAC address matches VM MAC for ingress, packets destination MAC address matches VM MAC for egress, packet source/destination MAC address matches VM MAC for both. If none option is chosen the dynamic counters will be uninstalled if it has been already installed, if not nothing happens.

extremeVMVPPVLANTag.name: extremeVMVPPVLANTag
extremeVMVPPVLANTag.description: VLAN Tag for Dynamic VLAN creation. For unset the value of 0 can be configured during that extremeVMVPPVLANVRName also be set to null string. If this parameter is not configured then 0 will be displayed . While setting this object if extremeVMVPPVLANVRName is not set then that will be assumed to have default value of VR-Default.

extremeVMVPPVLANVRName.name: extremeVMVPPVLANVRName
extremeVMVPPVLANVRName.description: The Virtual router name for Dynamic VLAN creation. VR-Mgmt cannot be specified and specified VR Name should be existing. By default VR-Default will be used. This object display non-null string only when extremeVMVPPVLANTag has non zero value. If this object is going to be configured after extremeVMVPPVLANTag has been configured for non zero value then this SET might be rejected if any of detected VM clients uses this VPP and these VPPs VR Name alone changes. Even though this object is specifically set to null string still this object display VR-Default if extremeVMVPPVLANTag has non zero value

extremeVMMappingTable.name: extremeVMMappingTable
extremeVMMappingTable.description: This table contains the mapping of port policies to virtual machine MAC addresses.

extremeVMMappingEntry.name: extremeVMMappingEntry
extremeVMMappingEntry.description: An entry in the table of VM information of this device.

extremeVMMappingType.name: extremeVMMappingType
extremeVMMappingType.description: The type of mapping for this entry. A local mapping exists only on this specific switch. A network mapping is one obtained via a download of a mapping file.

extremeVMMappingMAC.name: extremeVMMappingMAC
extremeVMMappingMAC.description: The MAC address associated with the Virtual Machine. Note that a VM may have multiple MAC addresses.

extremeVMMappingIngressVPPName.name: extremeVMMappingIngressVPPName
extremeVMMappingIngressVPPName.description: The ingress policy associated with the VM/MAC address. Note that this may refer to a policy without a corresponding entry in the extremeVMVPPTable if a network policy mapping refers to a non-existent policy. This would indicate an error in the policy mapping file that is consulted if network authentication fails. When creating an entry in this table, this name must refer to an existing, valid, local policy. The creation of a mapping to a network policy is not permitted. Those mappings must be created at the central policy server.

extremeVMMappingEgressVPPName.name: extremeVMMappingEgressVPPName
extremeVMMappingEgressVPPName.description: The egress policy associated with the VM/MAC address. Note that this may refer to a policy without a corresponding entry in the extremeVMVPPTable if a network policy mapping refers to a non-existent policy. This would indicate an error in the policy mapping file that is consulted if network authentication fails. When creating an entry in this table, this name must refer to an existing, valid, local policy. The creation of a mapping to a network policy is not permitted. Those mappings must be created at the central policy server.

extremeVMMappingStatus.name: extremeVMMappingStatus
extremeVMMappingStatus.description: Indicates the virtual port profile mapping status. vppValid(1) -> When VPP mapped to this VM MAC does not have any policies associated with it (or) all the policies associated with this VPP can be applied (policy validation is success). Policy validation will happen only when this VM MAC is detected. vppMissing(2)-> This value is applicable only for network VM if the specified VPP Name was missing. vppInvalid(3)-> When any one of polices mapped to VPP cannot be applied (policy validation failed) because the policy file contains one or more errors that prevent it from being applied vppNotMaped(4)-> If the VM does not have any VPP Mapped.

extremeVMMappingRowStatus.name: extremeVMMappingRowStatus
extremeVMMappingRowStatus.description: Only local virtual port profiles can be created or deleted.

extremeVMMappingVPPName.name: extremeVMMappingVPPName
extremeVMMappingVPPName.description: The virtual port profile associated with the VM/MAC address. When creating an entry in this table, this name must refer to an existing, valid, local profile. The creation of a mapping to a network profile is not permitted. Those mappings must be created at the central policy server.

extremeVMMappingVLANTag.name: extremeVMMappingVLANTag
extremeVMMappingVLANTag.description: VLAN Tag for Dynamic VLAN creation. For unset the value of 0 can be configured during that extremeVMMappingVLANVRName also be set to null string. If this parameter is not configured then 0 will be displayed . While setting this object if extremeVMMappingVLANVRName is not set then that will be assumed to have default value of VR-Default.

extremeVMMappingVLANVRName.name: extremeVMMappingVLANVRName
extremeVMMappingVLANVRName.description: The Virtual router name for Dynamic VLAN creation. VR-Mgmt cannot be specified and specified VR Name should be existing. By default VR-Default will be used. This object display non-null string only when extremeVMMappingVLANTag has non zero value. If this object is going to be configured after extremeVMMappingVLANTag has been configured for non zero value then this SET might be rejected if any of detected VM clients uses this mapping and these mapping VR Name alone changes. Even though this object is specifically set to null string still this object display VR-Default if extremeVMVPPVLANTag has non zero value

extremeVMVPP2PolicyTable.name: extremeVMVPP2PolicyTable
extremeVMVPP2PolicyTable.description: This table contains the mapping of a VPP to individual Policies.

extremeVMVPP2PolicyEntry.name: extremeVMVPP2PolicyEntry
extremeVMVPP2PolicyEntry.description: An individual mapping of VPP to Policy.

extremeVMVPP2PolicyPolicyName.name: extremeVMVPP2PolicyPolicyName
extremeVMVPP2PolicyPolicyName.description: The name of the local policy

extremeVMVPP2PolicyOrder.name: extremeVMVPP2PolicyOrder
extremeVMVPP2PolicyOrder.description: The order in which this policy will be executed

extremeVMVPP2PolicyRowStatus.name: extremeVMVPP2PolicyRowStatus
extremeVMVPP2PolicyRowStatus.description: The row status for this mapping.

extremeVMDetectedNumber.name: extremeVMDetectedNumber
extremeVMDetectedNumber.description: The number of virtual machines detected on this switch.

extremeVMDetectedTable.name: extremeVMDetectedTable
extremeVMDetectedTable.description: This table contains the currently detected VMs on this switch.

extremeVMDetectedEntry.name: extremeVMDetectedEntry
extremeVMDetectedEntry.description: An entry in the table of VM information of this device.

extremeVMDetectedMAC.name: extremeVMDetectedMAC
extremeVMDetectedMAC.description: The MAC address associated with the Virtual Machine. Note that a VM may have multiple MAC addresses.

extremeVMDetectedVMName.name: extremeVMDetectedVMName
extremeVMDetectedVMName.description: The name of the Virtual Machine. Note that a VM authenticated locally may not have a name.

extremeVMDetectedIngressVPPName.name: extremeVMDetectedIngressVPPName
extremeVMDetectedIngressVPPName.description: The name of the policy applied (or attempted to apply) to this virtual machine.

extremeVMDetectedEgressVPPName.name: extremeVMDetectedEgressVPPName
extremeVMDetectedEgressVPPName.description: The name of the policy applied (or attempted to apply) to this virtual machine.

extremeVMDetectedIfIndex.name: extremeVMDetectedIfIndex
extremeVMDetectedIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex on which this virtual machine was detected.

extremeVMDetectedAdminStatus.name: extremeVMDetectedAdminStatus
extremeVMDetectedAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of the Virtual Machine authentication. Setting this variable to authenticating(1) will force the re-authentication of the VM. This variable always returns idle(2) when read.

extremeVMDetectedOperStatus.name: extremeVMDetectedOperStatus
extremeVMDetectedOperStatus.description: The authentication status of the VM authenticating(1) an authentication is currently in progress authenticatedNetwork(2) the VM has been authenticated by a network source authenticatedLocally(3) the VM bas been authenticated by the local database denied(4) the VM was either explicitly denied entry notAuthenticated(5) the authentication process timed out or was never attempted.

extremeVMDetectedResultIngress.name: extremeVMDetectedResultIngress
extremeVMDetectedResultIngress.description: Indicates the result of a VM entry into the network. Only below two values will be returned at any point of time. policyApplied(1) - all the ingress policies in the VPP was successfully applied to the port. policyNotApplied(2) - If any one of the ingress policies in the VPP was not applied to the port. If this value is returned then refer to extremeVMDetectedIngErrPolicies object for list of failed ingress policies.

extremeVMDetectedResultEgress.name: extremeVMDetectedResultEgress
extremeVMDetectedResultEgress.description: Indicates the result of a VM entry into the network. Only below two values will be returned at any point of time. policyApplied(1) - all the egress policies in the VPP was successfully applied to the port. policyNotApplied(2) - If any one of the egress policies in the VPP was not applied to the port. If this value is returned then refer to extremeVMDetectedEgrErrPolicies object for list of failed egress policies.

extremeVMDetectedIngErrPolicies.name: extremeVMDetectedIngErrPolicies
extremeVMDetectedIngErrPolicies.description: Displays the list of failed ingress policies

extremeVMDetectedEgrErrPolicies.name: extremeVMDetectedEgrErrPolicies
extremeVMDetectedEgrErrPolicies.description: Displays the list of failed egress policies

extremeVMDetectedVPPName.name: extremeVMDetectedVPPName
extremeVMDetectedVPPName.description: The name of the VPP applied (or attempted to apply) to this virtual machine.

extremeVMDetectedVPPResult.name: extremeVMDetectedVPPResult
extremeVMDetectedVPPResult.description: Indicates the result of VPP associated with VM MAC. vppMapped(1) indicates that the named VPP was mapped. vppNotMapped(2) indicates that the no VPP was mapped. vppInvalid(3) indicates that the VPP mapped was invalid. vppMissing(4) indicates that the VPP mapped was missing.

extremeVMDetectedCounterInstallResult.name: extremeVMDetectedCounterInstallResult
extremeVMDetectedCounterInstallResult.description: Indicates the result of whether dynamic counter installed for this VM. ingress-only(1) - Dynamic counters are installed to count packet source MAC address matches VM MAC. egress-only(2) - Dynamic counters are installed to count packet destination MAC address matches VM MAC. both(3) - Dynamic counters are installed to count packet source/destination MAC address matches VM MAC. none(0) - Dynamic counters are not installed.

extremeVMDetectedVMVLANTag.name: extremeVMDetectedVMVLANTag
extremeVMDetectedVMVLANTag.description: VLAN Tag used for Dynamic VLAN creation for detected VM MAC. If this parameter is not configured then 0 will be displayed

extremeVMDetectedVMVLANVRName.name: extremeVMDetectedVMVLANVRName
extremeVMDetectedVMVLANVRName.description: The Virtual router name of the Dynamic VLAN created for detected VM MAC.

extremeVMVPPDetailTable.name: extremeVMVPPDetailTable
extremeVMVPPDetailTable.description: This table contains the mapping of a VPP to individual Policies.

extremeVMVPPDetailEntry.name: extremeVMVPPDetailEntry
extremeVMVPPDetailEntry.description: A set of mappings from a VPP to one or more policies.

extremeVMVPPDetailDirection.name: extremeVMVPPDetailDirection
extremeVMVPPDetailDirection.description: The direction in which the policy will be applied

extremeVMVPPDetailOrder.name: extremeVMVPPDetailOrder
extremeVMVPPDetailOrder.description: The order in which this policy will be executed

extremeVMVPPDetailPolicyName.name: extremeVMVPPDetailPolicyName
extremeVMVPPDetailPolicyName.description: The name of the local policy

extremeVMVPPDetailRowStatus.name: extremeVMVPPDetailRowStatus
extremeVMVPPDetailRowStatus.description: The row status for this mapping.

extremeVMVPPInvalid.name: extremeVMVPPInvalid
extremeVMVPPInvalid.description: A virutal port profile definition is invalid, indicating it cannot be applied to a port.

extremeVMMapped.name: extremeVMMapped
extremeVMMapped.description: This notification is generated whenever a MAC is manually mapped to a local policy.

extremeVMUnMapped.name: extremeVMUnMapped
extremeVMUnMapped.description: This notification is generated whenever a MAC is manually unmapped to a local policy.

extremeVMDetectResult.name: extremeVMDetectResult
extremeVMDetectResult.description: This notification is generated after a VM is detected on a port and reflects the result of that operation.

extremeVMUnDetectResult.name: extremeVMUnDetectResult
extremeVMUnDetectResult.description: This notification is generated after a VM is undetected (removed) from a port.
